The paper focuses on self-supervised representation learning for videos, specifically using temporal cycle consistency to find correspondences across time in multiple videos. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the learned embeddings for few-shot classification and compares the TCC method to other self-supervised learning methods, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses applications of the embeddings for transfer of metadata and anomaly detection, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
